        "show_top_divider": false,
        "reverse_layout": false,
        "caption": "",
        "body_text": "<p>The most common mistake in residential lighting is attempting to light the \"air\" in the center of the room. This results in the \"interrogation effect\"—harsh overhead shadows and a flat, sterile environment. The professional alternative is <em>Wall Washing</em>.</p>",
        "body_text_2": "<p>When light bounces off a matte surface like plaster or paint, it scatters. This scattered light is infinitely softer than direct light from a bulb. It creates a glow that flatters the room and the people in it. By washing the wall, the wall becomes the light source, eliminating the glare of a \"naked bulb\".</p>",
